stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> Disabled

    Disabled --> Unplugged : Enable
    Unplugged --> Disabled : Disable
    Plugged --> Disabled : Disable
    Charging --> Disabled : Disable

    Unplugged --> Plugged : Plug
    Plugged --> Unplugged : Unplug / BspEvent(Disconnected)

    state Active <<choice>>
    Plugged --> Active
    Active --> Charging : see ISO / AC IEC diagrams

    Plugged --> Faulted : InjectFault
    Charging --> Faulted : InjectFault
    Faulted --> Unplugged : ClearFault / Unplug

    note right of Disabled
        Every non-Faulted active state accepts Disable
        and routes to Disabled (SlacMatching,
        V2GNegotiating, BcbToggling, Paused, Stopping,
        ChargingPwmPaused too, not just the arrows
        shown). Faulted ignores Disable.
    end note
